Amazing pizza and friendly staff. They are always willing to go above and beyond for your business. Antipasto Salad was crisp with cold meat and the pizza was hot upon pickup and VERY cheesy. Their knots are also amazing also, but we didn‚Äôt get them this time. Definitely a great local spot for amazing food.

Eat here. Just do it. Pizza is on a crust that is crunchy on the outside and pillowy soft bready goodness that melts on the inside. The classic cheese pull. Burgers cooked to perfection on toasted buns. Tons of seating and parking, incredibly fast service and nice people!!

Really liked it! Nice view, good selection of beers on draft. The garlic knots were to die for! They give you a huge order! I could have eaten them all they were so good. Crispy on the outside, soft inside, garlicky and delicious. We had the fried chicken. It was cooked perfectly. We had come a couple years ago and it must have been an off day as it was dry and hard. Today was crispy, juicy and awesome! The best fried chicken we've had in years. The Jojo's are good if you like a big potato wedge. Very flavorful and crispy. Definitely our new fried chicken place! Can't wait to go back and try some other menu items.
Great pizza here. We got a meat pie and the white pizza. Both were delicious. They have several beers on tap and even a husband daycare.

detailedReviews.text: I moved to Florida, in 2005, from the Northeast. I always complain that I cannot get good pizza, hoagie/subs, etc. down here like I could up there. This was my first time going to 'Your Pizza Shop' even though they are less than 10 minutes away from my home. I am now mad at myself for missing out on excellent food since 2005. üôÇ My pepperoni, sausage, and black olive pizza is on par with what I would have gotten up north. I will definitely visit this establishment again and I highly recommend you do that same!

detailedReviews.author: Tyler Harn
detailedReviews.text:
Today, I witnessed a driver from Your Pizza Shop in a blue Hyundai Sonata driving extremely recklessly down 8th Avenue in Largo. The car was speeding, swerving, and blowing through intersections like the rules of the road didn‚Äôt apply. It was genuinely dangerous and could have caused a serious accident.

As someone who lives off 8th Ave, I won‚Äôt let this slide if it happens again. If I see this kind of driving one more time, I will immediately report it to the Largo Police Department or the Pinellas County Sheriff‚Äôs Office with no hesitation.

You‚Äôre lucky I‚Äôm giving you a chance to correct this. Handle it internally, hold your driver accountable, and make sure this doesn‚Äôt happen again. Because next time, law enforcement will be notified and involved.

Do better. Before someone gets hurt.
